# Frontend monorepo (`frontend/`)

pnpm workspace: `apps/*`, `packages/*`. Node **24+** ([`.nvmrc`](frontend/.nvmrc)), registry npmjs.org ([`.npmrc`](frontend/.npmrc)).

## Packages

| Path | Name | Role |
|------|------|------|
| `apps/admin/` | `@transora/admin` | HeroUI admin panel (Vite 8, React 19) |
| `packages/api-client/` | `@transora/api-client` | Orval-generated client + `mutator`, `auth-tokens` |

## Commands (from `frontend/`)

```bash
pnpm install --ignore-scripts
pnpm dev              # admin @ :5173
pnpm api:fetch        # curl live /v3/api-docs → openapi/transora.openapi.json (commit when API changes)
pnpm api:generate     # orval from committed openapi
pnpm api:sync         # fetch + generate
```

**Orval is mandatory.** Do not hand-edit `packages/api-client/src/generated/**`. Hand-written clients (`admin-catalog.ts`, `admin-route-pricing.ts`, …) are temporary until endpoints appear in OpenAPI and `pnpm api:sync` regen covers them.

After `api:fetch`, run `pnpm api:generate` and `pnpm exec tsc -b` in `apps/admin`. A larger live spec may rename Orval symbols (`list1` → `list2`); fix imports or add stable `operationId` on backend controllers before merging the openapi snapshot.

## Import aliases by package

- **Admin app**: `@/` → `src/` — see [frontend-admin.mdc](frontend-admin.mdc)
- **API client**: `@/` → `src/` — internal imports only; apps import the package as `@transora/api-client`

When adding a new app under `apps/`, configure `@/` in both `vite.config.ts` (`resolve.alias`) and `tsconfig` (`baseUrl` + `paths`).
